{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "24", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "19", "S": "09"}}, "news": [{"title": "UP-RERA to open April 1-15 window for QPR filings, warns of action for non-compliance", "para": "UP-RERA will open its portal for developers to submit quarterly progress reports from April 1 to April 15, 2026. This is mandatory for all registered projects. Developers must update project details within this period. Failure to submit these reports can lead to penalties. This ensures transparency for homebuyers. Recent actions show UP-RERA is enforcing these rules.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/up-rera-to-open-april-1-15-window-for-qpr-filings-warns-of-action-for-non-compliance/129777085?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-77512/129777085.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "Haryana RERA directs Imperia Structures to pay \u20b955 lakh compensation to homebuyers", "para": "Haryana RERA has ordered Imperia Structures to pay homebuyers \u20b955 lakh for lost property appreciation. The builder must also compensate for mental agony and litigation costs. Homebuyers booked an apartment in Gurugram's 'The Esfera' project in 2013. Possession was promised by May 2017 but was delayed. The authority previously ordered a refund of \u20b973.37 lakh.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/rera/haryana-rera-directs-imperia-structures-to-pay-55-lakh-compensation-to-homebuyers/129776928?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-148402/129776928.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "rera"}, {"title": "India\u2019s flex office stock crosses 100 million sq ft, demand driven by IT, GCCs: Report", "para": "Crossing the 100 million sq ft mark, India's flexible office space has witnessed remarkable expansion in just five years. At the helm is Bengaluru, boasting the highest concentration of flexible work environments. The surge in demand is primarily fueled by IT, technology, and BFSI industries, with international corporations taking the lead in space absorption.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/indias-flex-office-stock-crosses-100-million-sq-ft-demand-driven-by-it-gccs-report/129772481?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-272704/129772481.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}]}